            <div class="rajasthani-border">
                <h1>A Note from the Author & Designer</h1>
                <div class="author-section">
                    <div class="author-name">Kr. Rajvardhan Singh Badgujar</div>
                    <p class="first-para">Hello and welcome to the official website of Thikana Dhabla Ghosi. I am Kr.Sa. Rajvardhan Singh Badgujar, son of Thakur Sa. Suresh Singh Badgujar. Born and raised in Thikana Dhabla Ghosi, I am currently pursuing BCA from Govt. Holkar Science College, Indore. Through my studies in web development, I have gained knowledge about front-end technologies, which inspired me to create this digital platform.</p>
                </div>
                
                <blockquote>
                    In vain have you acquired knowledge if you do not impart it to others.
                </blockquote>
                
                <p>
                    Being from the field of web development, I felt it was my moral responsibility to create a website to showcase the royal culture and heritage we belong to. With the proliferation of computer technology around the world, the internet serves as the best medium to connect people and share knowledge. So, please feel free to spread the word and let everyone know about the rich culture and glorious history of the Badgujar Rajput family of Thikana Dhabla Ghosi.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="acknowledgement-section">
                <h1>🙏 Acknowledgements</h1>
                <div class="rajasthani-pattern">
                    <p>Creating this website has been a fulfilling journey, and it would not have been possible without the support and encouragement of many individuals. I would like to take this opportunity to express my heartfelt gratitude to all those who have contributed directly or indirectly to this project.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="acknowledgement-item">
                    <h3>🏰 Family Support</h3>
                    <p>First and foremost, I extend my deepest thanks to my beloved father, <strong>Thakur Sa.Suresh Singh Badgujar</strong>, and my respected mother, for their unwavering support and for instilling in me a deep sense of pride in our heritage. Their stories, teachings, and guidance about our royal culture and traditions have been the foundation of this website. I am also grateful to all my family members who encouraged me throughout this journey.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="acknowledgement-item">
                    <h3>🌾 Community Contributions</h3>
                    <p>A special thanks to the esteemed elders and residents of Thikana Dhabla Ghosi, who generously shared their knowledge, stories, and valuable insights about our rich culture, history, and ancestral traditions. Their contributions have added depth, authenticity, and a personal touch to this platform, helping preserve our legacy for future generations.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="acknowledgement-item">
                    <h3>💻 Technical & General Appreciation</h3>
                    <p>I am thankful to my professors at Govt. Holkar Science College, Indore, for their guidance in web development. I also appreciate the support of friends who provided feedback and encouragement. Lastly, thank you to every visitor of this website—your interest in our heritage keeps our traditions alive.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="signature-box">
                    <p><strong>With warm regards,</strong><br>
                    <strong>Kr. Sa. Rajvardhan Singh Badgujar</strong><br>
                    Thikana Dhabla Ghosi,<br>
                    District Shajapur, Madhya Pradesh</p>
                </div>
            </div>
